ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now let me check if there are any issues with the SwipeCardStack gest
ure handling. Looking at the code:\n\n1. The `SwipeCardStack` uses `GestureDetec
tor` with `onHorizontalDragStart`, `onHorizontalDragUpdate`, `onHorizontalDragEn
d`.\n2. But the action buttons (`SwActionButton`) are separate and outside the c
ard stack in `HomePageSkeleton`.\n3. The design spec says: "左滑/点击 ✕ → Pass",
"右滑/点击 ♥ → Like"\n\nHowever, looking at the `SwipeCardStack`, when a user sw
ipes, the animation completes and then `widget.onSwipe` is called. The parent (`
HomePageSkeleton`) removes the card from `_cards` in `_onSwipe`. But there\'s a 
subtle issue: when the swipe animation is running, the card is still in `_cards`
, so if the user rapidly taps the action buttons while animation is running, it 
could cause issues. Also, the `SwipeCardStack` doesn\'t prevent interaction duri
ng animation.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at `_onDragEnd`:\n```dart\nif 
(shouldSwipe && widget.cards.isNotEmpty) {\n  _exitDirection = ...\n  _isAnimati
ng = true;\n  _pendingSwipeCard = widget.cards.last;\n  _pendingSwipeDirection =
_exitDirection;\n  _controller.forward(from: 0);\n}\n```\n\nAnd in `_buildCardLa
yer`, for the front card:\n```dart\nreturn AnimatedBuilder(\n  animation: _contr
oller,\n  builder: (context, child) {\n    final animationValue = _controller.va
lue;\n    final exitOffset = _exitDirection == SwipeDirection.left\n        ? -c
onstraints.maxWidth * 1.5\n        : constraints.maxWidth * 1.5;\n    final curr
entOffset = _isAnimating\n        ? _dragPosition + (exitOffset - _dragPosition)
* animationValue\n        : _dragPosition;\n    ...\n  },\n);\n```\n\nBut the Ge
stureDetector is still active during animation! Since `_isAnimating` is not chec
ked in `onHorizontalDragStart` or `onHorizontalDragUpdate`, a second drag could 
start while the first animation is running. This is a bug.\n\nAlso, there\'s ano
ther issue: when `widget.cards` is updated from the parent (via setState after `
onSwipe` is called), the widget rebuilds. But since `onSwipe` is called AFTER th
e animation completes (in `_onAnimationStatusChanged`), the card is removed afte
r animation. That\'s good.\n\nHowever, looking at the `GestureDetector` in `Swip
eCardStack`: it wraps the whole Stack. If there are no cards, it returns `SizedB
ox.shrink()` but still wrapped in GestureDetector. That\'s fine.\n\nWait, let me
also look at the import in `widgetbook/main.dart`:\n```dart\nimport \'../../../d
esigns/issue-43/flutter-widgets/widgetbook/widgetbook_use_cases.dart\';\n```\n\n
This is an import from `packages/design-system/widgetbook/main.dart` to `designs
/issue-43/flutter-widgets/widgetbook/widgetbook_use_cases.dart`. The relative pa
th `../../../designs/issue-43/` goes from `packages/design-system/widgetbook/` t
o the repo root, then into `designs/issue-43/`. This is technically valid but it
\'s a cross-package import that violates normal package boundaries. Since `desig
ns/` is not a Dart package, this import might fail in some build contexts. Howev
er, for a Design-Only PR, this is a practical way to preview the widgets.\n\nBut
AGENTS.md explicitly says for Design-Only PR:\n> `.dart` 资产必须放在 `designs/i
ssue-XXX/flutter-widgets/`，禁止直接写入 `packages/` 或 `apps/`\n\nAnd the templ
ate says:\n> Flutter Widget 代码: `designs/issue-XXX/flutter-widgets/`（**禁止**
直接写入 `packages/` 或 `apps/`）\n\nSo modifying `packages/design-system/widget
book/main.dart` and `packages/design-system/lib/src/theme/tokens.dart` directly 
is a clear violation of the Design-Only PR boundary. These changes should be doc
umented in the MANIFEST.md for a subsequent feat PR to apply.\n\nWait, but `flut
ter.md` says:\n> Design-Only PR 的变更范围仅限于：\n> - `packages/design-system/
`（新增/修改组件）\n> - `packages/design-system/widgetbook/main.dart`（注册展示
用例）\n> - `apps/mobile/lib/presentation/` 中的纯 UI 骨架\n\nSo there\'s an exp
licit conflict between:\n1. AGENTS.md (top-level): "`.dart` 资产必须放在 `design
s/issue-XXX/flutter-widgets/`，禁止直接写入 `packages/` 或 `apps/`"\n2. TEMPLATE
-design.md: "Flutter Widget 代码: `designs/issue-XXX/flutter-widgets/`（**禁止**
直接写入 `packages/` 或 `apps/`）"\n3. flutter.md: "Design-Only PR 的变更范围仅
限于：packages/design-system/..."\n\nWhich one takes precedence? The AGENTS.md s
ays "仓库即唯一真实来源". AGENTS.md is the entry point. Also, the TEMPLATE-desig
n.md is specifically for design tasks and explicitly prohibits writing to packag
es/. The `flutter.md` might be describing an older or different interpretation.\
n\nActually, looking more carefully at `flutter.md`, it says:\n> 1. 只修改 `pack
ages/design-system/` 和 `apps/mobile/lib/presentation/`\n\nBut this is under the
"Design-Only PR 流程" section. However, AGENTS.md (which is the navigation map) 
clearly says:\n> 设计任务 ≠ 美术任务。Design-Only PR 必须产出 `.dart` 纯 UI Widg
et + `MANIFEST.md` 迁移清单 + Widgetbook 用例代码 + Golden Test 代码。\n> `.dart
` 资产必须放在 `designs/issue-XXX/flutter-widgets/`，禁止直接写入 `packages/` 或
`apps/`\n\nThis seems like a clear rule. The fact that `flutter.md` contradicts 
it might be an inconsistency in the project docs, but as a reviewer, I should fl
ag violations of explicit rules from the top-level AGENTS.md.\n\nActually, wait 
- looking at the commit history, commit `a5f6ca6` is "docs: clarify .dart asset 
location for Design-Only PRs (#50)". This suggests PR #50 was specifically about
clarifying this rule. And the current branch diverged from that. So the AGENTS.m
d rule about `.dart` assets in `designs/issue-XXX/flutter-widgets/` is the newer
, clarified rule.\n\nGiven that, modifying `packages/design-system/lib/src/theme
/tokens.dart` and `packages/design-system/widgetbook/main.dart` directly in this
PR is a violation.\n\nHowever, the `MANIFEST.md` acknowledges these as "迁移注意
" items. The proper workflow should have been:\n1. Design-Only PR creates the de
sign assets in `designs/issue-43/` ONLY\n2. A subsequent feat PR migrates them t
o `packages/` and `apps/`\n\nSo this is a workflow violation, but the code quali
ty itself is good. Let me decide how to grade this.\n\nAlso, let me check the E2
E test file. The `.maestro/flows/matching/swipe_and_match.yaml` is an E2E flow. 
For a Design-Only PR, is E2E expected? The design template doesn\'t mention E2E 
as a required output. The `flutter.md` E2E section says:\n> 任何涉及用户交互流程
的 Mobile 变更，必须遵守 `docs/design-docs/testing.md` 中的 Mobile UI E2E 测试（
Maestro）规范\n\nBut for a Design-Only PR, there is no actual UI in the app yet 
- the widgets are in `designs/` directory. So the Maestro flow cannot actually r
un against the app. The Maestro flow references `id: "pass_button"` etc., which 
don\'t exist in the actual app since the widgets are only design assets. This is
premature and incorrect for a Design-Only PR. E2E flows should be added when the
widgets are actually integrated into the app.\n\nLet me check the `apps/mobile/a
ssets/images/.gitkeep` file. This is a new file. Why would a design PR add a `.g
itkeep` to the app\'s assets? The design spec says "本设计全部使用 Emoji / 矢量
图标 / CSS 渐变占位，无需额外图片资源". So this file is unnecessary and touches 
`apps/mobile/` which is prohibited.\n\nNow let me look at specific code issues:\
n\n1. **SwipeCardStack gesture during animation**: As noted, `_isAnimating` is n
ot checked in drag handlers. If user swipes while animating, it could reset `_dr
agStartX` and cause weird behavior.\n\n2. **SwipeCardStack `onNeedMoreCards` tim
ing**: It calls `_maybeRequestMoreCards()` after animation completes, but it che
cks `widget.cards.length < 3`. However, at that point, the parent hasn\'t remove
d the swiped card yet because `onSwipe` is called first (in `_onAnimationStatusC
hanged`), then `_maybeRequestMoreCards` is called. Wait, let me re-read:\n```dar
t\nif (status == AnimationStatus.completed) {\n  ...\n  if (_pendingSwipeCard !=
null && _pendingSwipeDirection != null) {\n    widget.onSwipe?.call(_pendingSwip
eCard!, _pendingSwipeDirection!);\n    _pendingSwipeCard = null;\n    _pendingSw
ipeDirection = null;\n  }\n  _maybeRequestMoreCards();\n}\n```\n\nActually, `wid
get.onSwipe` is called BEFORE `_maybeRequestMoreCards`. But `widget.onSwipe` tri
ggers a setState in the parent which removes the card. By the time `_maybeReques
tMoreCards` runs, the widget might have already been rebuilt with the new card l
ist. Since this is in the same animation completion callback, and Flutter schedu
les setState rebuilds, the exact timing depends. This is probably fine because `
_maybeRequestMoreCards` checks `widget.cards.length` which reads the latest prop
s after rebuild. But it\'s a bit fragile.\n\nActually, there\'s a bigger issue: 
`widget.onSwipe` is called inside `AnimationStatus.completed` listener. This cal
lback runs synchronously when the animation completes. The parent\'s `setState` 
will schedule a rebuild. But `_maybeRequestMoreCards` runs immediately after `wi
dget.onSwipe`, still in the same frame, before the rebuild happens. So `widget.c
ards` still has the old length! This means if there were exactly 3 cards, after 
swipe there should be 2, and `onNeedMoreCards` should fire. But because `widget.
cards` hasn\'t been updated yet (setState is scheduled), `widget.cards.length` i
s still 3, so it won\'t fire.\n\nWait, actually in Flutter, when you call `setSt
ate` in another widget, that widget\'s state is marked dirty and will rebuild in
the next frame. But the current frame (where the listener is running) hasn\'t en
ded yet. So `widget.cards` in this widget still points to the old list. Therefor
e `_maybeRequestMoreCards` will see the old length.\n\nThis is a real bug. If yo
u have 3 cards and swipe one, `widget.cards.length` is still 3 when `_maybeReque
stMoreCards` runs, so it won\'t trigger. Only when you swipe the next card (goin
g from 3 to 2, but the parent hasn\'t updated yet... wait, no - after the first 
swipe\'s setState completes, the next time you interact, `widget.cards` will hav
e 2 cards. Then when you swipe again, `widget.cards.length` will be 2 during ani
mation, and after animation + onSwipe, it\'ll still be 2, so `_maybeRequestMoreC
ards` WILL fire.\n\nActually wait, if you start with 3 cards:\n- Swipe 1: animat
ion ends, onSwipe called (parent setState to remove 1 card), _maybeRequestMoreCa
rds sees length=3 (old), doesn\'t fire\n- Next frame: parent rebuilds, this widg
